Class JIPExistenceException

  • java.lang.Object

        • java.lang.RuntimeException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class JIPExistenceException
extends JIPRuntimeException
    Author:
    Ugo Chirico an existence error occurs when an object on which an operation is to be performed does not exist. ErrorTerm has the following form: existence_error(Object, Culprit) where Object is the type of the object and Culprit the argument which caused the error. Object is one of: procedure source_sink stream
